  "doc_id": "prion_0671",
  "text": "In a patient with Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (Heidenhain type), which was characterized by the initial onset of visual symptoms and proved by autopsy, there was an antagonizing correlation between spontaneously-induced periodic synchronous discharges and photically induced giant evoked responses.\nIn addition, the two electroencephalogram features appeared and disappeared in parallel with each other during the clinical course of the illness.",
